{
  "stem": "6736.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we were on appellplatz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "On the place where you, you get together.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I stood with my brother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we had on our clothing a-- a-- a-- a sign as a Jew and a number.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he took my brother's number down.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "My brother had something here on his throat.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So maybe it caught his eye.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he regi-- signed up all the-- he marked up all the children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And a week later they took him to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And a few days later they took my brother, my two cousins, Esther, my uncle's two children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we hid in Plaszow from 1943 in March, to 1944 in May, 14 months.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And he-- to get food for them, and to carry the stuff out from them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And in May, we almost-- the war was coming to an end.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But he couldn't save the two children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And so I was left with the little boy, little brother, who worked on the barges in the Vistula.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "In October and November, the Vistula froze.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So there was no more work.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "People-- the barges were on a stand still.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "So my brother had no place to sleep.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So he went out in the hills.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And there were-- but the shepherds kept a [NON-ENGLISH] and food for the animals.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And he slept there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And any time a big snowstorm was through the night, in the morning as he was going down, he make snow steps.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And a Polish fellow grabbed him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "He said, you must be Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Because if you're not Jewish, you wouldn't be sleeping in, in [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And he also knew the-- the prayers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "He spoke a beautiful Polish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And they took him the police.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And they pulled the pants down.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And for that the Polish fellow received five pounds of sugar.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
